text: Kly Mod 18-3: at HV turn on, immediately get repeated klystron OV + OC faults on MKSU. Station holds off HV without triggers, but with triggers, never get station on with aforementioned faults. LOTO'd station and opened thyratron compartment to look at pulse cable. Nothing seen there. Checked BNC connections on klystron tank (volts/amps readbacks)--cleaned connectors which had oil and greenish corrosion on them. Checked klystron tank connections at back of MKSU: good. Attempted to run up station again: got a loud bang from thyratron comparment. Discovered the EOLC busbar attached from the CT standoff to the floating panel of the PFN cap case had a small gap between the busbar and the panel. Part of copper from the bar had welded to the aluminum of the panel. The mounting screw head had been eaten away and the busbar was making poor contact. It's obvious arcing was occuring at this connection. Classic case of galvanic corrosion. Removed damaged busbar. Retrieved spare busbar and installed. Drilled and tapped a new mounting hole on the PFN case panel and moved the busbar over from the original mount hole which has welded copper on it. See log entry for photo. Station now comes up and sounds very good! No faults. Adjusted BV to spec. CATER ready to close. --chw, sj

title: Getting S-band modulator to run at 10 Hz while station 2 is at 30Hz.
text: S-band modulator rate is observed and limited by the MPS/ BCS CAMAC module in Ta02 CR mod 8.Currently this module takes a trigger from TA02 CR slot 21 STB channel 1 (Trig 201). If this rate goes above 10 HZ the module in slot 8 cuts off the fiber output that goes to the NIM crate in rack 39 level 23 slot 11. This NIM module accepts the fiber output from module 8. It outputs a trigger to the modulator . When station 2 wants to go above 10 Hz to 30Hz . an operator goes to the RLAREA panel on the SCP and selects the NLCTA FULLRT button on the lower left corner of the panel. This puts all the TRIGs in TA01,TA02 and TA03 that have the beam condition no_gun_perm_ DEACT. condition on them to 30 HZ. Currently this includes the trigger for the S-band modulator TRID 201 which goes to 30 HZ . The module in crate 8 detects this higher rate and stops the trigger going to the modulator. To avoid this I propose that we switch the gun trigger from TRIG 201 to TRBR 202 which is currently unused. This TRBR (Trigger Base Rate) has been programed for 10Hz. A TRBR puts out its programmed trigger rate regardless of any beam condition. In this way station 2 can run at any rate and S-band will still be at 10Hz. Comments?
